# Chart Selection Rules

## MAPPING

IF data is categorical vs numeric → USE bar chart  
IF data is time-based → USE line chart  
IF data is distribution → USE histogram / KDE / boxplot  
IF data is correlation → USE scatter plot  
IF data is part-to-whole → USE stacked bar (NOT pie if >5 categories)

## HARD CONSTRAINTS

- Bar charts MUST start at zero
- Line charts MUST use ordered x-axis
- Pie charts ONLY if <=5 categories

## ANTI-PATTERNS

- DO NOT use line chart for categorical x-axis
- DO NOT use pie chart with similar values
- DO NOT distort axis scales